The goal of this project is to create a glue-dispensing jig to aid in the assembly of a polymer heat exchanger. Our project aims to achieve autonomy and decrease human error in adhesive application between injection-molded ABS MPHX plates and PC lamina. The glue-dispensing jig consists of a jig to hold the MPHX plates, an adhesive applicator, a lamina applicator, a clamping mechanism, and an auto-feeding mechanism to apply glue to the plates in a organized, effective, and efficient way. The glue dispensing jig will be used to seal plates for large-scale production. An emphasis is made on the jigs accuracy and effectiveness when gluing the plates and lamina together to create leak-free channels through sealing.

